Benchmark Set: float-UnboundedLoop (Java)
Benchmark Name: Adjustable-Inner-Count-Halving
Description:
This benchmark is part of the "float-UnboundedLoop" collection proposed
for SV-COMP 2026. It focuses on verifying floating-point computations
that involve unbounded or data-dependent loops, where the number of
iterations cannot be statically determined.

Purpose:
The benchmark is designed to evaluate the capability of Java verification
tools (such as JBMC, JayHorn, and Jay-Sym) to reason about numeric
operations performed inside unbounded control structures. Typical patterns
include threshold-based switching, rounding, normalization, and
accumulation over floating-point variables.

Expected Property:
ReachSafety-assert (all assertions must hold)

Safety Note:
All benchmarks in this collection are SAFE with respect to the declared
properties — both 'valid-assert' and 'no-runtime-exception'. These programs
do not violate any safety assertions and are free from runtime exceptions.